cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.CY, cs.SI

This paper deals with network security and privacy, specifically in the context of communication between hosts on the Internet. The use of cryptographic tokens and the involvement of ISPs suggest a focus on network infrastructure and protocols, which is consistent with the Computer Science categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses practical considerations for deployment, which could fall under the categories of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
